.TH "gmap_shadow_r3t" 9 "gmap_shadow_r3t" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gmap_shadow_r3t \- create a shadow region 3 table
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gmap_shadow_r3t
.BI "(struct gmap *sg "  ","
.BI "unsigned long saddr "  ","
.BI "unsigned long r3t "  ","
.BI "int fake "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sg" 12
pointer to the shadow guest address space structure
.IP "saddr" 12
faulting address in the shadow gmap
.IP "r3t" 12
parent gmap address of the region 3 table to get shadowed
.IP "fake" 12
r3t references contiguous guest memory block, not a r3t
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 if successfully shadowed or already shadowed, -EAGAIN if the
shadow table structure is incomplete, -ENOMEM if out of memory and
-EFAULT if an address in the parent gmap could not be resolved.

Called with sg->mm->mmap_lock in read.
